h Airlines aircraft at Dulles International Airport in Dulles, Virginia, on February 14, 2023. The World Health Organization said February 14, 2023 that last week's massive earthquake, the epicentre of which was in Turkey, constituted the "worst natural disaster" in 100 years in its Europe region. The confirmed death toll following the earthquake stands at 35,331. A local resident attempts to salvage his car from the rubble of collapsed buildings in Hatay, on February 14, 2023, after a 7.8-magnitude earthquake struck the country's south-east. The death toll from a catastrophic earthquake that hit Turkey and Syria nears 40,000 on February 14, 2023, with search and rescue teams starting to wind down their work. This aerial view shows collapsed buildings during ongoing rescue operations in Kahramanmaras, southeastern Turkey, on February 14, 2023, eight days after a 7,8-magnitude struck the country's southeast. The death toll from a catastrophic earthquake that hit Turkey and Syria nears 40,000 on February 14, 2023, with search and rescue teams starting to wind down their work. Damages cars sit parked by the rubble of collapsed buildings in Hatay, on February 14, 2023, after a 7.8-magnitude earthquake struck the country's south-east. The death toll from a catastrophic earthquake that hit Turkey and Syria nears 40,000 on February 14, 2023, with search and rescue teams starting to wind down their work. This aerial view shows collapsed buildings during the ongoing rescue operation in Kahramanmaras, in southeastern Turkey, on February 14, 2023, after a 7.8-magnitude earthquake struck the country's south-east. The death toll from a catastrophic earthquake that hit Turkey and Syria nears 40,000 on February 14, 2023, with search and rescue teams starting to wind down their work. This picture shows a collapsed building in the Islahiye district of Gaziantep on February 15, 2023 after a 7,8-magnitude earthquake on February 6 has killed at least 35,000 people and devastated swathe